  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">LACT - Climate Change Adaptation in Bolivia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With the support of Latin American Children&apos;s Trust and local partner organisations, Oxfam has implemented a climate change adaptation project in Beni for the last 10 years. The project supported peasant and indigenous families living in secluded flood -prone areas, to improve their living standards through climate resilient agricultural production and flood proof housing and schools.  Despite considerable achievements in the technical aspects of the agricultural and housing components (climate resilient agricultural production in place to support 61 families, 100 raised houses and 2 schools built), the end of project evaluation highlighted weaknesses in the area of sustainability. In order to address this crucial area and ensure that communities are able to benefit durably from the progress achieved to date, Oxfam proposes a 12 -month project to work specifically on the following areas:  - organisational strengthening of communities  - strengthening of agricultural/fish productivity  - transfer of skills and experience to local governments</narrative>
  </description>
